Ayoola Bakare and Koya Onagoruwa, organisers of the Ayko Agency Talent Hunt, have revealed plans for the annual event. The organisers restated that the annual event is aimed at discovering and nurturing raw African talents and showcasing them to the world. The talent hunt which cuts across music, acting, modeling, and dancing has officially opened entries for interested persons.   Jaruma remanded after Regina Daniel’s husband petition     I suck at showing interest in people – Ex-BBNaija’s…     Sammie Okposo pulls down apology post   The brains behind the event noted that the hunt is interested in discovering talents and giving them the necessary support. “From the very beginning, we had sought to ensure that emphasis was placed on upskilling and supporting the talents and models to the very highest standards, giving them every opportunity to proudly represent the best of the industry, on the world stage. - Advertisement - “We are looking to identify talents (actor/actress, singer/musician, painter/sketch artist, dancer, etc.) and models, with true potential. You must be over 18 years old and can come from any corner of Nigeria,” said the co-founders, Koya Onagoruwa and Ayoola Bakare. They further noted that registration is now open to interested persons from the age of 18 and above until Friday, April 15, 2022, while the grand finale holds on Friday, May 13, 2022, in Lagos.